## What Problem This Solves

`extensions/discord/src/api.ts:198` calls `JSON.parse(text)` on the raw Discord API response body without try/catch protection. If Discord returns a 200 with malformed JSON (e.g. due to a proxy error, CDN glitch, or gateway misconfiguration), the unhandled `SyntaxError` propagates up through `retryAsync` and crashes the calling code path instead of being handled gracefully.

This is a **D4** defense-in-depth fix: crash → graceful degradation via `DiscordApiError`.

## Changes

- `extensions/discord/src/api.ts`: wrap `JSON.parse(text)` in try/catch; throw `DiscordApiError("malformed JSON")` on parse failure so the error follows the same handling path as HTTP errors
- `extensions/discord/src/api.test.ts`: 1 new test verifying malformed JSON success bodies throw `DiscordApiError`

**Scope**: `requestDiscord` success-path JSON parse only (1 line). The error-body path already uses `readResponseTextLimited`.

Label: bugfix | merge-risk: 🟢 minimal | AI-assisted

## Evidence

### Unit test

```
pnpm exec vitest run extensions/discord/src/api.test.ts --reporter=verbose

 ✓ throws DiscordApiError on malformed JSON success response body
 ... (all existing tests continue to pass)

 Test Files  1 passed (1)
```

### Before/after

```
// Before: unhandled SyntaxError crash
const text = await res.text().catch(() => "");
return JSON.parse(text) as T;  // 💥 SyntaxError → process crash

// After: graceful DiscordApiError
try {
  return JSON.parse(text) as T;
} catch (cause) {
  throw new DiscordApiError("Discord API ${path} returned malformed JSON", 0);
  // ↓ handled by retryAsync / caller like any other DiscordApiError
}
```

### Why status=0

A malformed JSON response is not an HTTP error (the server returned 200) and is not retryable (the body will be malformed on retry too). `status=0` ensures `shouldRetry` skips it.
